4 A JOINT RESOLUTION OF THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
5 MONTANA APPLYING FOR A CONVENTION OF THE STATES UNDER ARTICLE V OF THE
6 CONSTITUTION OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE PURPOSE OF PROPOSING AN AMENDMENT TO
7 THE CONSTITUTION TO SET TERM LIMITS ON MEMBERS OF CONGRESS.
8
9 WHEREAS, Article V of the Constitution of the United States provides the states with the authority to
10 call an amendment convention for the purpose of proposing an amendment to the Constitution of the United
11 States on application by at least two-thirds of the states; and
12 WHEREAS, this power provides the states with the leverage needed to force Congress to act when it
13 otherwise does not want to; and
14 WHEREAS, the citizens of Montana overwhelmingly support term limits on members of Congress; and
15 WHEREAS, the Legislature of the State of Montana hereby joins with other states in instructing
16 Congress to draft a term limits amendment and send it to the states for ratification, failing which the states will
17 act on their own; and
18 WHEREAS, the Montana Legislature, a body of citizen legislators, desires to restore rotation in office
19 for members serving in the United States Congress.
20
21 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
22 THE STATE OF MONTANA:
23 (1) That pursuant to Article V of the Constitution of the United States, the Legislature of the State
24 of Montana formally applies to the United States Congress to call a convention limited to proposing an
25 amendment to the Constitution of the United States to set a limit on the number of terms a person may be
26 elected as a member of the United States House of Representatives and as a member of the United States
27 Senate.
28 (2) That the Secretary of State of the State of Montana transmit copies of this resolution to the
