5 (3) That this application be considered as covering the same subject matter as the applications
6 from other states to Congress to call a convention to set a limit on the number of terms that a person may be
7 elected to the United States House of Representatives and the United States Senate, and that this application
8 be aggregated with the applications of other states for the purpose of attaining the two-thirds of states
9 necessary to require Congress to call a limited convention for the purpose of setting term limits on the members
10 of Congress, but that this application not be aggregated with any other application on any other subject.
11 (4) That this resolution constitutes a continuing application in accordance with Article V of the
12 Constitution of the United States until the legislatures of at least two-thirds of the states have made applications
13 on the same subject.
